Management is an intensive, interactive and practical course that consists of three modules: manager and employee (managerial roles, managerial job, values, attitudes, work motivation, organisational culture), manager and team (project management, group development and group roles, trust in team), and manager and organization (financial management, strategic management, analysis of external and internal environment). 
To complete this course in volume 3 ECTS the student chooses two modules out of three. 

The course is based on various interactive, creative and analytical methods of teaching (i.e. set of lectures, seminars, written assignments, group assignments). The participants are expected to prepare for every class in accordance of the proposed plan.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to acquire and develop managerial knowledge and skills for understanding and managing teams and organizations.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has successfully completed this course in volume 6 ECTS has acquired all following learning outcomes and student who has successfully passed this course in volume 3 ECTS has acquired four learning outcomes out of the following: 1. Understands the values, attitudes and motivation of an individual related to work and work environment as well as their impact on the functioning of the organisation. 2. Understands organisational culture and how human resources policies affect it. 3. Understands the phases of Project Management, team and team functioning principles and has acquired teamwork experience. 4. Has solved the problems related to organisational communication, including those affecting organisational image. 5. Is able to see the organisation in its entirety and is able to analyse its environment. 6. Understands the basic principles of financial management of an organisation and indicators of economic performance in the context of strategic management. Additionally, the student is able to creatively formulate theoretical and practical problems of organisational management and offer solutions to them. Upon completion of the course in volume 6 ECTS the student has applied selected methods of managerial work in (knowledge-intensive) organization.
